Their egg and cheese sandwiches are incredible and very filling. It may sound silly, but I truly appreciate that these guys really listen because they’re the only place that doesn’t have a problem putting S, P, K, & hot sauce on my sandwich. Every other place ignores my request and throws in ketchup and hot sauce packets instead which drives me nuts. The delivery is usually VERY fast and the delivery guys never complain or refuse to come upstairs; they’re always very pleasant. Their iced coffee is always really good. I highly recommend ordering food from here. You can’t go wrong!

I just left this market completely turned off!  I ordered the 2 egg platter with eggs over medium, beef sausage and hash browns.  When i receieved my order the person at the counter and gave me a side of hash browns.  I asked him why did he give me homefries and hashbrowns, the menu said either or and I selected hashbrowns.  I figured it was a honest mistake but I didnt want to be charged for that mistake.  The person took the container of food back, opened it, removed my eggs over medium and beef sausage with his barehands and placed it in another container.  The yoke broke and the eggs were now destroyed and smashed in the corner of the container.  I was completely grossed out by the fact that he didnt have on gloves and was cross contaminating food.  He then made someones sandwich without washing his hands.  I checked the hands of the others behind the counter and they had on gloves!  After he handed the container over to me, I proceeded to the counter...hungry as hell...but not hungry enough to ingest germs or bacteria!  I handed it over to the cashier and told him that I can not pay for the food and told him what had happened.  I walked home...sad...breakfastless....and now I am eating oatmeal.
